# SQS operations

## Dead-Letter Queue (DLQ)

Failed too many times → set `maxReceiveCount` (3–5) → SQS moves it to the DLQ (same type as source).

- **Poison messages** shunted aside → queue keeps moving
- **Audit log of failures** → inspect, fix, **redrive** back to source

## Long polling

`WaitTimeSeconds` 1–20 → wait for a message vs. return empty (short poll). **Cuts empty receives, cost, latency** — the default.

## Delays & large messages

- **Delay queues** — postpone visibility up to **15 min** (queue-wide or per-message timer)
- **> 256 KB** → **Extended Client**: body in **S3**, reference in the queue
